tasks.description:
Create two hand-written idempotent SQL files in `packages/db/src/migrations/extras/`:

`018-social-indexes.kind.sql`:
```sql
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_social_posts_status ON social_posts(status);
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_social_posts_next_run_at ON social_posts(next_run_at) WHERE next_run_at IS NOT NULL;
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_social_post_targets_status ON social_post_targets(status);
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_social_audit_log_entity ON social_audit_log(entity_type, entity_id);
CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_social_publish_logs_post ON social_publish_logs(social_post_id, created_at DESC);
```

`019-social-set-updated-at.trigger.sql`:
For each of the 14 tables with `updated_at` (all except the append-only trio: social_ai_requests, social_publish_logs, social_audit_log), register the `set_updated_at` trigger using `CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS` following the pattern of existing extras files.

Run `pnpm db:apply-extras` to verify both files are idempotent (can run twice without error).

Test requirements:
- Run `pnpm db:apply-extras` twice; no errors on second run
- Verify indexes appear in `\di+ social_*` in psql

Create `packages/service-core/src/services/social/social-audit-log.service.ts`.

Single exported method:
```ts
log(params: {
  actorId: string | null;
  eventType: string;
  entityType: string;
  entityId: string;
  oldValue?: Record<string, unknown>;
  newValue?: Record<string, unknown>;
  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
}): Promise<void>
```

Writes one row to `social_audit_log`. Must never throw — wrap in try/catch and log error with `@repo/logger` if the DB write fails (so an audit log failure never blocks a state transition).

Also export a const `SocialAuditEvent` object mapping all event type strings (POST_APPROVED, POST_REJECTED, POST_CHANGES_REQUESTED, POST_SCHEDULED, POST_RESCHEDULED, POST_MARKED_READY, POST_PAUSED, POST_UNPAUSED, POST_ARCHIVED, HASHTAG_PROMOTED, PLATFORM_FORMAT_UPDATED, SETTING_UPDATED, TARGET_PUBLISHED, TARGET_PUBLISH_FAILED, TARGET_DISPATCH_FAILED_EXHAUSTED) for type safety.

Test requirements:
- Unit tests: log() creates a row, log() swallows DB errors without rethrowing
- File: `packages/service-core/src/services/social/__tests__/social-audit-log.test.ts`
